<H1>Saving command history between logins</H1>

<P>Whenever you logout or exit from the Bourne Again SHell
the contents of your command history are saved in the
file <SAMP>.bash_history</SAMP> in your home directory.</P>

<P>When you next login the contents of this file are placed
in the history list and you can re-use commands from your
previous login session.</P>

<P>To specify how much of your command history is to be
saved <A HREF="../environment/index.html">set the environment variable</A>
<SAMP>HISTFILESIZE</SAMP>. For example:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   <STRONG>HISTFILESIZE=25;export HISTFILESIZE</STRONG>
</PRE>

<P>This saves the previous twenty-five (25) commands you
have used; not the complete command history list.</P>

